      "content": "wait, so u're saying the safety net is basically just an \"attractive option\" for people who can already afford it? that sounds like it might be downplaying how many people actually rely on those programs to survive. wouldn't some people argue that a stronger safety net actually helps people get better jobs by giving them stability instead of just making them want to quit?",
